#X obj 526 264 asr~ 0 2000, f 21;
#X text 227 149 Decay;
#X text 613 209 'Decay';
#X text 28 375 The arguments set the attack \, decay \, sustain point and release parameters. Hence \, you can see we have the decay parameter set to "2000" ms. The 4th inlet sets the decay parameter as well. The decay stage \, by default is non linear \, simliar to but not like the [decay~] object. There's also a curve factor that sets this exponential curve (same as with the [smooth~] object. The object has more features \, it also has a 'lag' mode \, which is in fact a one-pole filter like [decay~]. You can see above it also has a status right outlet \, which shows when the envelope is done., f 58;
#X obj 761 314 vsl 16 100 0 1 0 0 empty empty empty 0 -9 0 10 #dcdcdc #000000 #000000 0 1;
